Package org.openwms.common.transport

Class TypePlacingRule

java.lang.Object
org.ameba.integration.jpa.BaseEntity
org.openwms.common.transport.TypePlacingRule
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, org.ameba.integration.TypedEntity<Long>, Rule
@Entity public class TypePlacingRule extends org.ameba.integration.jpa.BaseEntity implements Serializable, Rule
A TypePlacingRule is a Rule that defines which types of TransportUnits (TransportUnitTypes) can be put on which type of Location (LocationType).

A privilegeLevel is defined to order a list of allowed LocationTypes.

Author:
Heiko Scherrer

    • privilegeLevel

      private int privilegeLevel
      The privilegeLevel defines a priority to describe which TransportUnitType can be placed on which LocationType.

      A value of 0 means the lowest priority. Increasing the privilegeLevel implies a higher priority and means the TransportUnitType can be placed to the LocationType with the highest privilegeLevel.

      To forbid a TransportUnitType on a certain LocationType the privilegeLevel must be set to -1.

      (not-null)
